-- Basic Energy, ICBC, Ngiu Kee: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview
-- B y   H a n n y   W a n
-- 2010-09-21T21:40:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/basic-energy-icbc-ngiu-kee-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in  Asian trading , excluding Japan.
Stock symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Basic Energy Corp.  (BSC PM): The Philippine producer of
ethanol and other alternative energy resources reached a
settlement agreement on the termination of a joint venture with
Ecomarket Farms Inc., a stock-exchange filing showed. The stock
fell 0.6 percent to 16.5 centavos.  Glomac Bhd.  (GLMC MK): The Malaysian property developer
said profit in the first quarter ended July 31 rose 87 percent
from a year earlier to 15.6 million ringgit ($5 million) as
sales surged. Glomac was unchanged at 1.46 ringgit.  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China Ltd.  (601398 CH): The
nation’s biggest listed lender said shareholders approved a plan
to raise as much as 45 billion yuan ($6.7 billion) from a rights
offer to replenish capital. The stock added 0.3 percent to 3.97
yuan on Sept. 20 before trading was suspended.  International Container Terminal Services Inc.  (ICT PM):
The largest Philippine port operator took over the operations of
a reefer facility in the Port of Davao, the company said in an
e-mailed statement. The stock fell 0.4 percent to 38.95 pesos.  Ngiu Kee Corp.  (NKC MK): The Malaysian supermarket operator
said it scrapped its proposed capital reduction plan because it
has joined the stock exchange’s list of troubled companies,
meaning it has to come up with a “comprehensive” plan to
restore its finances or risk being de-listed. The stock was
unchanged at 4.5 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Hanny Wan  in Hong Kong at 
 hwan3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net . 